.TH HSH 1 "29 April 2025" "1.0" "hsh manual page"
.SH NAME
hsh \- Simple UNIX command-line interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a lightweight UNIX command-line interpreter designed for executing basic user commands. Developed as a trimester final project at Holberton School, it introduces core shell functionalities such as command execution, process management, and error handling.
.SH OPTIONS
None.
.SH USAGE
.B hsh
launches an interactive shell interface displaying the prompt "NM$" (customizable) to accept user commands. Commands are executed upon entering a newline.
.SH FUNCTIONALITY
.B hsh
supports the following features:
.IP "\fB1. Prompt Display\fR"
Displays the "NM$" prompt (configurable) and awaits user input. Commands must end with a newline.
.IP "\fB2. Command Execution\fR"
Executes user-entered commands.
.IP "\fB3. Error Handling\fR"
Handles errors (e.g., "command not found") by printing an error message and redisplaying the prompt. Also manages the "end of file" condition (Ctrl+D).
.IP "\fB4. Command Arguments\fR"
Supports commands with arguments.
.IP "\fB5. PATH Handling\fR"
Utilizes the PATH environment variable to locate executable files.
.IP "\fB6. Built-in Commands\fR"
Implements
.B exit
and
.B env
built-in commands.
.IP "\fB7. Exit Command\fR"
The
.B exit
command terminates the shell. Usage:
.B exit
(no arguments).
.IP "\fB8. Env Command\fR"
The
.B env
command displays the current environment variables.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
.B $ ./hsh
.br
NM$ ls
.br
./shell: No such file or directory
.br
NM$ /bin/ls
.br
barbie_j  env-main.c  exec.c  fork.c  pid.c  ppid.c  prompt  prompt.c  shell.c  stat.c  test_scripting.sh  wait.c
.br
NM$ exit
.PP
.B $ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
.br
barbie_j  env-main.c  exec.c  fork.c  pid.c  ppid.c  prompt  prompt.c  shell.c  stat.c  test_scripting.sh  wait.c
.SH EXIT STATUS
.B hsh
returns:
.IP 0
Successful execution.
.IP 1
Execution error.
.SH FILES
None.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR bash(1),
.BR sh(1),
.BR execve(2),
.BR fork(2),
.BR wait(2),
.BR access(2)
